      "*": "{{Sort}}\n{{Chapter Box\n|title = The Great Adventure of Usopp the Man\n|jname = 男ウソップ大冒険\n|rname = Otoko Usoppu Daibōken\n|ename = The Great Adventure of Usopp the Man\n}}\n'''Chapter 70''' is titled \"The Great Adventure of Usopp the Man\".\n\n==Cover Page==\n[[Cover Page#Color Spread|Color Spread]]: The [[Straw Hat Pirates]] as samurai, all dressed in {{W|Kabukimono}}-esque clothing and all wielding at least one sword. [[Monkey D. Luffy|Luffy]] in particular is perched on an upside-down wok, holding an {{W|Oil-paper umbrella|oil-paper parasol}} while unsheathing his red-lacquered sword with his teeth.\n\n==Short Summary==\n[[Roronoa Zoro|Zoro]] arrives at [[Arlong Park]]. [[Nojiko]] is introduced and revealed to be [[Nami]]'s sister.\n\n==Long Summary==\n[[Roronoa Zoro|Zoro]], [[Usopp]] and [[Johnny]] arrive in front of [[Arlong Park]]. In order to prevent Zoro from foolishly attacking the [[fish-men]], he's tied up by Johnny and Usopp while they search for the [[Going Merry]]. They soon found it anchored near a local village. Usopp, who acted bravely once away from Arlong Park, becomes a coward again once he notices three Fish-Men next to the boat. He and Johnny flee into the sea once they have been spotted, leaving Zoro alone and powerless in front of the Fish-Men.\n\nWhen Usopp and Johnny pull themselves out of the sea, they notice that the village has been completely devastated and postulate it was destroyed by the Fish-Men. They are impressed by the power of these creatures. They find one of the Fish-Men has returned to the village, suspicious of Zoro being alone. While Johnny is able to hide himself, Usopp starts running until he bumps into a kid, [[Chabo]], and a woman, [[Nojiko]]. When the Fish-Man is about to capture them, Usopp decides to act bravely for once, and tries to defend the two villagers, but is knocked out by Nojiko.\n\nWhen he wakes up, the three of them are in Nojiko's house, in an orange farm. Nojiko tells them that nobody fights the fish-men because it's suicide. Chabo, a boy from [[Gosa Village]], whose father has been killed, understands this, and returns to his mother rather than seeking revenge.\n\nUsopp understands that Nojiko's intentions are not bad, and tells her that he is looking for [[Nami]]. Nojiko then tells Usopp that Nami and her are adopted sisters, and that Nami is a member of [[Arlong Pirates]].\n\n==Quick Reference==\n===Chapter Notes===\n*[[Roronoa Zoro|Zoro]], [[Usopp]], and [[Johnny]] arrive at [[Cocoyasi Village]], the site of [[Arlong Park]].\n*[[Nojiko]] is introduced, and reveals that she and [[Nami]] are stepsisters.\n\n===Characters===\n{| class=\"CharTable\"\n!colspan=\"2\"| [[Pirate]]s\n! Citizens\n! [[Bounty Hunter]]s\n|-\n|\n;[[Straw Hat Pirates]]\n*[[Monkey D. Luffy]] ''(cover)''\n*[[Roronoa Zoro]]\n*[[Nami]] ''(cover)''\n*[[Usopp]]\n*[[Sanji]] ''(cover)''\n|\n;[[Arlong Pirates]]\n*[[Arlong]] ''(image)''\n*[[Hatchan]] ''(shadowed)''\n*[[Nami]] ''(image)''\n|\n;[[Gosa Village]]\n*[[Chabo]]\n----\n;[[Cocoyasi Village]]\n*[[Nojiko]]\n|\n*[[Johnny]]\n|}\n\n==Author Comment==\n{{WSJ Comment}}\n\n==Trivia==\n*In the chapter's initial publishing in [[Shonen Jump|''Weekly Shonen Jump'']], the first page was printed in full color.\n*Although Nami currently is with [[Arlong Pirates|Arlong's crew]], she appears on the story as one of the [[Straw Hat Pirates]].\n*This is the first chapter where [[Luffy]] only appears on the cover.\n\n==Site Navigation==\n{{Arlong Park Arc}}\n[[de:Otoko Usopp Daibōken]]"
